<br>
2) Don't pull. If you pull, you get an extra couple of agro points just for that. Taunting off will be next to impossible given your equipment if you pull. <br>
<br>
3) Don't backstab right away. Wait for a few seconds before hitting it. Perhaps evade just prior to hitting BS to lower you even more on list. <br>
<br>
4) Turn off melee every 6 seconds or so for a couple seconds. Let the tanks catch up to you agro wise.<br>
<br>
5) Make sure your healer is on the ball, in case 1,2 or 3 fail. <br>
<br>
Be happy you have the gear you do. Treat the extra agro as a status symbol, albeit a painful one. <br>
<br>
I have silver chitin hand wraps and some descent weps. Agro is a problem, but nothing an evade can't solve. <br>
